    <title>Navigation Bar</title>
<section xml:id="navigation-bar-description"><title>Navigation Bar</title>
    <para>The Editor allows the ability to modify content, create content, view content, create
            versions, and export content. One of the areas to access these functions is in the
            navigation bar. </para>
    <para><figure xml:id="navigation-bar">
        <title>Navigation Bar</title>
        <mediaobject>
            <alt>Figure of the Knowledge Editor navigation displaying the Editor logo, and
                menu options for Projects, Export Management, Authoring, Manager, and User
                name Admin</alt>
            <imageobject>
                <imagedata align="left" scalefit="1" width="40%" contentdepth="40%"
                    fileref="images/nav-editor-layout2.png"/>
            </imageobject>
        </mediaobject>
    </figure></para>
    <para>The navigation bar provides the following options:<itemizedlist>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Projects - If your account has more than one project assigned, switch
                        between them by selecting this menu item.</para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Shortcuts - Used for multiple actions that can be found in tab-specific
                        areas of the application.</para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Manager - this option takes you to the Knowledge Manager Homepage. For the
                        content editor and manager, account settings can be modified here; for the
                        admin, user permissions and info are located
                        here.<?oxy_insert_start author="mnham" timestamp="20200326T112440-0700"?>
                        This option is not visible to read-only and edit-only
                        users.<?oxy_insert_end?></para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>User - the menu under the user's name provides the ability to update
                        global settings, manage account,
                        <?oxy_insert_start author="mnham" timestamp="20200326T112720-0700"?>find
                        application help, <?oxy_insert_end?>and to log out.</para>
                </listitem>
            </itemizedlist></para>
    <section><title>Projects</title>
       <para>T<?oxy_delete author="mnham" timestamp="20200326T113742-0700" content="his menu"?><?oxy_insert_start author="mnham" timestamp="20200326T113742-0700"?>he
                projects menu<?oxy_insert_end?> displays the projects that a user is assigned to.
                The user can switch between projects with this menu option as long as there
                <?oxy_insert_start author="mnham" timestamp="20200326T113759-0700"?>are<?oxy_insert_end?><?oxy_delete author="mnham" timestamp="20200326T113759-0700" content="is"?>
                more than one project assgined, and the Knowledge environment they are working in
                has more than one project defined. The default is to have one project per Knowledge
                instance.</para></section>
    <section>
            <title>Shortcuts</title>
            <para>The shortcuts submenu provides a quick way for the user to access certain actions.
                These include:<itemizedlist>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>Create a version – displays the create a version
                            modal.<?oxy_insert_start author="mnham" timestamp="20200326T114801-0700"?>
                            This option is only visible to users with content manager permissions
                            and above.<?oxy_insert_end?></para>
                    </listitem>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>Export content – displays the export content modal.</para>
                    </listitem>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>New concept – to create a new concept.</para>
                    </listitem>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>New map set – to create a new map set.</para>
                    </listitem>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>New value set – to create a new value set.</para>
                    </listitem>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>Run classifier – performs a classification run.</para>
                    </listitem>
                   <listitem>
                        <para>Run QA test – performs a quality assurance check. </para>
                    </listitem>
                </itemizedlist>
                <figure xml:id="shortcuts">
                    <title>Shortcuts Menu</title>
                    <mediaobject>
                        <alt/>
                        <imageobject>
                            <imagedata align="left" fileref="images/shortcuts-menu2.png"/>
                        </imageobject>
                    </mediaobject>
                </figure>All of these actions can be performed by going through the shortcut menu or
                through features within specific tabs and panels in the <emphasis>task
                    pane</emphasis>, refer to <xref linkend="editor-functions"
                />.<?oxy_comment_start author="susancastillo" timestamp="20200324T181504-0700" comment="reference will display when a .pdf is generated for the whole user guide."?></para><?oxy_comment_end?>
        </section>
            
    <section>
            <title>Manager</title>
            <para>The Manager option is only available to an <emphasis>Administrator</emphasis> or
                    <emphasis>System Manager</emphasis> administrator.
                <?oxy_insert_start author="mnham" timestamp="20200326T125849-0700"?>When<?oxy_insert_end?><?oxy_delete author="mnham" timestamp="20200326T125848-0700" content="If"?>
                selected<?oxy_insert_start author="mnham" timestamp="20200326T125852-0700"?>,<?oxy_insert_end?>
                the user will be taken to the Knowledge Manager area.
                Here<?oxy_insert_start author="mnham" timestamp="20200326T125857-0700"?>,<?oxy_insert_end?>
                a user with the appropriate permissions can modify user accounts, create new
                accounts, etc. for more details refer to <xref linkend="user-management"/>
                <?oxy_comment_start author="susancastillo" timestamp="20200324T181356-0700" comment="the reference here will display when a .pdf for the whole user guide is generated."?></para><?oxy_comment_end?>
        </section>
    
    <section><title>Username Menu</title>
        <para>The menu under the user's name provides the ability to modify global settings, manage
                your account, view the user guide, request technical support, and log out of the
                application, <xref linkend="user-menu"/>.<itemizedlist>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>Global Display Settings – contains filters and customizations for what is
                            displayed throughout the user interface.</para>
                    </listitem>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>Manage Account – enables a user to modify their user profile.</para>
                    </listitem>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>Help – user documentation for Knowledge.</para>
                    </listitem>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>Contact Technical Support – send a technical support request.</para>
                    </listitem>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>Logout – signs you out of Knowledge.</para>
                    </listitem></itemizedlist>
          </para>
          <para><figure xml:id="user-menu">
            <title>User Menu</title>
            <mediaobject>
                <alt></alt>
                <imageobject>
                    <imagedata align="left" 
                        fileref="images/user-menu-options.png"/>
                </imageobject>
            </mediaobject>
        </figure></para>
        
        <section><title>Global Display Settings</title>
            <para>When a user is
                    created<?oxy_insert_start author="mnham" timestamp="20200326T135740-0700"?>,<?oxy_insert_end?>
                    the display options are configured with <emphasis>default</emphasis> settings. A
                    user can modify the display settings using the <emphasis>Global Display
                        Settings</emphasis>
                    <footnote>
                        <para>There are other display options in the Global Display Settings panel
                            that are not fully implemented and will not be documented here. It is
                            recommended that users <emphasis role="strong">ONLY</emphasis> modify
                            settings that are documented in this section</para>
                    </footnote> panel. Changes to the display settings in the <emphasis>Global
                        Display Settings</emphasis> panel affects the displayed information in both
                    the <emphasis>Task Pane</emphasis> and the <emphasis>Concept Viewer
                        Pane</emphasis>, refer to <xref linkend="editor-functions"/>. However, the
                        <emphasis>Concept Viewer Pane</emphasis> and the <emphasis>Task
                        Pane</emphasis>
                    <emphasis role="strong">can override</emphasis> the <emphasis>Global Display
                        Settings</emphasis> using the <emphasis>Display Options</emphasis> located
                    in the top right hand corner of each pane. The configurable options in
                        <emphasis>Global Display Settings</emphasis> are: <itemizedlist>
                        <listitem>
                            <para>General Options – a user can change the order in which the
                                descriptions are displayed in the taxonomy view and the number of
                                concepts displayed in the taxonomy.</para>
                        </listitem>
                        <listitem>
                            <para>Display Options – a user can configure the properties displayed,
                                stated or inferred views of the taxonomy, and modules.</para>
                        </listitem>
                    </itemizedlist>
                </para>
            <section><title>General Options</title>
                <para>In the default configuration FQN is the preferred description to display in
                        the taxonomy, the taxonomy will display
                        250<?oxy_insert_start author="mnham" timestamp="20200326T140806-0700"?>
                        children<?oxy_insert_end?> concepts
                        <?oxy_delete author="mnham" timestamp="20200326T140813-0700" content="deep"?><?oxy_insert_start author="mnham" timestamp="20200326T140822-0700"?>per
                        concept (additional ones are available through
                        pagination)<?oxy_insert_end?>, and the language is English, are shown in
                            <xref linkend="general-display-options"/> outlined in red.</para>
                <para><figure xml:id="general-display-options">
                    <title>General Display Options</title>
                    <mediaobject>
                        <alt></alt>
                        <imageobject>
                            <imagedata align="left" scalefit="1" width="75%" contentdepth="75%"
                                fileref="images/general-global-display-options.png"/>
                        </imageobject>
                    </mediaobject>
                </figure></para></section>
             
            <section><title>Display Options</title>
                <para><?oxy_delete author="mnham" timestamp="20200326T141033-0700" content="Like"?><?oxy_insert_start author="mnham" timestamp="20200326T141033-0700"?>Similar to<?oxy_insert_end?>
                        <emphasis>General
                        Options</emphasis><?oxy_insert_start author="mnham" timestamp="20200326T141039-0700"?>,<?oxy_insert_end?>
                        the <emphasis> Display Options</emphasis> are set to default settings when a
                        user's account is
                        created<?oxy_insert_start author="mnham" timestamp="20200326T141047-0700"?>
                        (<?oxy_insert_end?><?oxy_delete author="mnham" timestamp="20200326T141046-0700" content=", "?>see
                            <xref linkend="display-options"/> areas circled in
                        red<?oxy_insert_start author="mnham" timestamp="20200326T141051-0700"?>)<?oxy_insert_end?>.
                        These options mostly effect the views in the <emphasis>Concept
                            Viewer</emphasis> and the <emphasis>Taxonomy</emphasis>.</para>
                <para><figure xml:id="display-options">
                    <title>General Display Options</title>
                     <mediaobject>
                         <alt></alt>
                         <imageobject>
                             <imagedata align="left" scalefit="1" width="75%" contentdepth="75%"
                                 fileref="images/global-display-options.png"/>
                         </imageobject>
                      </mediaobject></figure> </para>
                <example><title>Display Inactive Descriptions</title>
                <para>To show inactive descriptions in the taxonomy and in the concept viewer
                                <emphasis role="bold">deselect</emphasis> the <emphasis>Show Only
                                Active Concepts</emphasis> checkbox, and select <emphasis>Apply
                                changes</emphasis>. Inactive
                            descriptions<?oxy_insert_start author="mnham" timestamp="20200326T141242-0700"?>
                            are italicized in the application, see
                            <?oxy_insert_end?><?oxy_delete author="mnham" timestamp="20200326T141304-0700" content=" in "?>the
                            screen shot below
                            <?oxy_insert_start author="mnham" timestamp="20200326T141309-0700"?>where
                            they <?oxy_insert_end?>are outlined in green.<mediaobject>
                                <alt/>
                                <imageobject>
                                    <imagedata align="left" scalefit="1" width="75%"
                                        contentdepth="75%"
                                        fileref="images/inactive-concepts-descriptions-displayed.png"
                                    />
                                </imageobject>
                            </mediaobject>
                        </para></example>
            </section>
        </section>
         <section><title>Manage Account</title>
            <para>A user can modify their account profile by selecting <emphasis>Manage
                        Account</emphasis><?oxy_insert_start author="mnham" timestamp="20200326T142208-0700"?>.<?oxy_insert_end?>
                    <?oxy_delete author="mnham" timestamp="20200326T142209-0700" content="f"?><?oxy_insert_start author="mnham" timestamp="20200326T142209-0700"?>F<?oxy_insert_end?>rom
                    there<?oxy_insert_start author="mnham" timestamp="20200326T142212-0700"?>,<?oxy_insert_end?>
                    the <emphasis>Edit Profile</emphasis> is presented, see <xref
                        linkend="user-edit-profile"/>. A user can modify
                    th<?oxy_delete author="mnham" timestamp="20200326T142317-0700" content="ere"?><?oxy_insert_start author="mnham" timestamp="20200326T142317-0700"?>eir<?oxy_insert_end?>
                    email address, User Name, Display Name, and password. To save changes to your
                    profile<?oxy_insert_start author="mnham" timestamp="20200326T142328-0700"?>,<?oxy_insert_end?>
                    select the <emphasis>save</emphasis> button. To return to the Knowledge Editor<?oxy_insert_start author="mnham" timestamp="20200326T142335-0700"?>,<?oxy_insert_end?>
                    <?oxy_delete author="mnham" timestamp="20200326T142342-0700" content="go to"?><?oxy_insert_start author="mnham" timestamp="20200326T142342-0700"?>select<?oxy_insert_end?>
                    your user
                    menu<?oxy_insert_start author="mnham" timestamp="20200326T142351-0700"?> at the
                    top right,<?oxy_insert_end?>
                    <?oxy_delete author="mnham" timestamp="20200326T142400-0700" content="and "?>select
                        <emphasis>Home</emphasis><?oxy_insert_start author="mnham" timestamp="20200326T142404-0700"?>,<?oxy_insert_end?>
                    then select <emphasis>Editor</emphasis> button. <note>
                        <para>The <emphasis>System Token</emphasis>is needed only by
                                <emphasis>Software Developers</emphasis>.</para>
                    </note>
                </para>
             <para><figure xml:id="user-edit-profile">
                 <title>Edit Profile</title>
                 <mediaobject>
                     <alt></alt>
                     <imageobject>
                         <imagedata align="left" scalefit="1" width="75%" contentdepth="75%"
                             fileref="images/user-edit-profile.png"/>
                     </imageobject>
                 </mediaobject>
             </figure></para>
         </section>
         <section><title>Help</title>
             <para>Selecting <emphasis>Help</emphasis> will open the 
                 <emphasis>User Documentation</emphasis> for 
                 <emphasis>Knowledge</emphasis> </para></section>
         <section><title>Contact Technical Support</title>
            <para>Selecting <emphasis>Contact Technical Support</emphasis> will bring the user to a
                    web-page where they can send their
                    question<?oxy_insert_start author="mnham" timestamp="20200326T142535-0700"?>
                    and<?oxy_insert_end?><?oxy_delete author="mnham" timestamp="20200326T142535-0700" content=","?>
                    describe their issue to our technical support team, <xref linkend="tech-support"
                    />. An email response will be sent to the user as soon as possible.</para>
             <para><figure xml:id="tech-support">
                 <title>Contact Technical Support</title>
                 <mediaobject>
                     <alt></alt>
                     <imageobject>
                         <imagedata align="left" scalefit="1" width="75%" contentdepth="75%"
                             fileref="images/tech-support.png"/>
                     </imageobject>
                 </mediaobject>
             </figure></para>
         </section>
    </section>
    </section>  
        
